 more compatible with the democratic ideal. What emerges is an emphatic call to action to reinvigorate our ailing democracies, and a road map for widespread institutional reform.Democratic Equality highlights the importance of diverse forms of authority in democratic deliberation and electoral and representative processes-and demonstrates how that authority rests equally with each citizen in a democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDemocracy. 0aEquality. 0aWelfare state. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishz978311061055008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691194141zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691194141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691194141.jpg  a978-3-11-061055-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPHb2019